race.description: The Valley @ Southside Pakenham Maiden Plate
race.comment: SHAPENAPIT (11) has shown ability in three runs to date, trying hard at Mornington last time behind a talented winner. She should relish the rise to 1100m here from the soft draw and will take plenty of holding out. INVINCIBLE LOVER (8) is the clear danger. She ran a good race off a slow speed on debut at Cranbourne over 1000m, beaten just a long neck in a strong effort. She'll be better for that and go close. FUNDAMENTAL NATURE (5) is a filly by Exceedance on debut for the Ciaron Maher yard. She was close up in a recent jump out and should be ready to go. AFTERBERNA (4) resumes having run a solid race on debut at Cranbourne when in the market. Expect improvement over the break and she's jumped out well. KIWI HARMONY (9) struggled fresh when in the market but could be an improver.
